OL,3,CLandowner targeted in fly-tipping
OL,4,C'epidemic'
OL,6,F"It costs a shedload of money on
OL,7,Faverage north of one thousand pounds,
OL,8,Fyou have to pay to take it to the tip
OL,9,Fand there are also the environmental
OL,10,Fissues caused by the waste."
OL,12,FDan is determined to find those
OL,13,Fresponsible for this fly-tip and any
OL,14,Fmore that happen on his land.
OL,16,F"I wouldn't say I'm desensitised to it
OL,17,Fbut it's happened a lot and I hate it
OL,18,Fand it's horrible to see and spoils a
OL,19,Flovely bit of countryside when it does
OL,20,Fhappen. It is criminal in every sense
OL,21,Fof the word."
